data.enText: the state of being like sb/sth but not exactly the same

data.chText: 这份报告强调两组之间的相似性。
data.enText: The report highlights the similarity between the two groups.
She bears a striking similarity to her mother.

data.chText: 他们的演唱风格有点像。
data.enText: There is some similarity in the way they sing.

data.chText: 两人都是医生，但他们的相似之处仅此而已。
data.enText: They are both doctors but that is where the similarity ends.

data.chText: 相像处；相似点；类似的地方
data.enText: a feature that things or people have that makes them like each other

data.chText: 对这两个国家的异同点的研究
data.enText: a study of the similarities and differences between the two countries

data.chText: 空手道比赛和拳击比赛有许多类似的地方。
data.enText: The karate bout has many similarities to a boxing match.

simple_means.memory_skill: similar 同样的；相似的 + ity 具备某种性质，状况 → 类似

tr: a Gestalt principle of organization holding that (other things being equal) parts of a stimulus field that are similar to each other tend to be perceived as belonging together as a unit

value.def: If there is a similarity between two or more things, they are similar to each other.

example.ex: The astonishing similarity between my brother and my first-born son...
example.tran: 我弟弟和我的大儿子长得惊人地相似

example.ex: There was a very basic similarity in our philosophy...
example.tran: 我们的人生哲学在根本上很相似。

example.ex: She is also 25 and a native of Birmingham, but the similarity ends there.
example.tran: 她也是 25 岁，也是伯明翰本地人，但也就这么多相似点了。

value.def: Similarities are features that things have which make them similar to each other.

example.ex: There were significant similarities between mother and son...
example.tran: 母子之间有很多相像的地方。

example.ex: The similarities between Mars and Earth were enough to keep alive hopes of some form of Martian life.
example.tran: 火星和地球之间的诸多相似处足以让人们对火星上存在某种生物抱以希望。

value.tran: 相似处;相似点;类似的地方
